Author::::TBombadil
DateTime::::2016-03-06T23:37:48Z
The atmosphere is warming at about 0.16C per decade. There was no let up in the steadily rising trend after 1998 and there will be no let up in the trend for many years after 2016. On top of that trend are short term fluctuations caused by El Ninos, La Ninas, volcanoes and solar cycles. They are interesting but largely irrelevant to the key statistic, the rising trend of about 0.16C per decade. 



